1
00:00:10,167 --> 00:00:11,700
<i>- Where are you going?
- Son...</i>

2
00:00:11,833 --> 00:00:14,033
<i>- I'm going back to Hazel.
- No!</i>

3
00:00:14,167 --> 00:00:16,800
<i>What if he changed his mind
and doesn't show up?</i>

4
00:00:16,933 --> 00:00:18,167
<i> Manuel will come.</i>

5
00:00:18,300 --> 00:00:20,767
<i>Because if he doesn't,
Coleen will rot in jail.</i>

6
00:00:20,900 --> 00:00:22,167
<i>- Andrea! Coleen!
- Jeff!</i>

7
00:00:22,300 --> 00:00:23,733
<i>Fine, I won't leave,
I'll stay here.</i>

8
00:00:23,867 --> 00:00:25,000
<i>I won't go back
to Hazel anymore.</i>

9
00:00:25,133 --> 00:00:26,633
<i>But we should prepare ourselves</i>

10
00:00:26,767 --> 00:00:27,800
<i>for the possibility that Coleen
might end up in prison.</i>

11
00:00:27,933 --> 00:00:29,133
<i> Welcome to our new home.</i>

12
00:00:29,267 --> 00:00:30,133
<i> What do you want?</i>

13
00:00:30,267 --> 00:00:31,400
<i> Let's talk for a bit.</i>

14
00:00:31,533 --> 00:00:33,333
<i>- Come on, just for a while.
- No, Hazel, I'm sleepy.</i>

15
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:34,900
<i> Jeff, you smell like alcohol!</i>

16
00:00:35,033 --> 00:00:36,667
<i>What? Did you
and Dad drink last night?</i>

17
00:00:36,800 --> 00:00:38,667
<i>Dad's gone,
he's with Hazel.</i>

18
00:00:38,800 --> 00:00:40,733
<i> Why is Dad with Hazel now?</i>

19
00:00:40,867 --> 00:00:42,100
<i> Jeffrey, come on!</i>

20
00:00:42,233 --> 00:00:43,633
<i> Get your siblings out of here!</i>

21
00:00:43,767 --> 00:00:45,067
<i> My head hurts!</i>

22
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:46,300
<i> Jeff, just tell us.</i>

23
00:00:46,433 --> 00:00:47,333
<i> What do you know?</i>

24
00:00:47,467 --> 00:00:49,033
<i> Wait! Fine, fine!</i>

25
00:00:49,167 --> 00:00:50,433
<i> Okay, I'll tell you.</i>

26
00:00:56,767 --> 00:00:59,700
<i>Jeff, don't you dare
tell your siblings.</i>

27
00:01:00,667 --> 00:01:02,233
<i> Especially not Coleen.</i>

28
00:01:02,367 --> 00:01:03,767
<i> Dad, what's the big deal?</i>

29
00:01:04,667 --> 00:01:06,300
<i> Why keep it from them?</i>

30
00:01:06,433 --> 00:01:07,567
<i> Because if Coleen finds out</i>

31
00:01:07,733 --> 00:01:10,033
<i> about my agreement with Hazel,</i>

32
00:01:10,167 --> 00:01:12,933
<i> she'll blame herself.</i>

33
00:01:13,067 --> 00:01:14,900
<i>Especially once she learns
she's the reason</i>

34
00:01:15,033 --> 00:01:17,567
<i> I have to go back to Hazel.</i>

35
00:01:17,700 --> 00:01:20,267
<i>So you'll just
let her be angry at you?</i>

36
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:22,800
<i> I'd rather she gets angry</i>

37
00:01:22,933 --> 00:01:24,067
<i> than feel guilty.</i>

38
00:01:24,933 --> 00:01:27,867
<i> Anger fades, son.</i>

39
00:01:28,933 --> 00:01:30,500
<i> But the guilt...</i>

40
00:01:30,633 --> 00:01:33,367
<i> you'll carry it for life.</i>

41
00:01:33,500 --> 00:01:37,567
<i> Coleen is such a good kid.</i>

42
00:01:37,700 --> 00:01:39,767
<i>She doesn't know
how to hold grudges.</i>

43
00:01:39,900 --> 00:01:41,933
<i> That's why I'm sure someday,</i>

44
00:01:42,100 --> 00:01:43,933
<i>she'll forget she was mad at me.</i>

45
00:01:45,767 --> 00:01:48,400
<i>Dad, I don't even know
what to tell them as the reason.</i>

46
00:01:49,800 --> 00:01:51,567
<i> I can't think of anything.</i>

47
00:01:51,700 --> 00:01:53,133
<i> I know one.</i>

48
00:01:54,733 --> 00:01:56,067
Hazel's hurting herself.

49
00:01:57,733 --> 00:01:59,467
She took a lot
of sleeping pills,

50
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:01,333
so they rushed her to the
hospital.

51
00:02:01,467 --> 00:02:03,100
Just because of that,
he's going back to Hazel?

52
00:02:03,933 --> 00:02:05,267
He actually believed her?

53
00:02:06,100 --> 00:02:08,400
He fell for her act?

54
00:02:08,533 --> 00:02:11,000
Sweetie, I saw Hazel
when I dropped Dad off.

55
00:02:12,267 --> 00:02:13,367
She looked awful,

56
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:14,833
like she wasn't even herself.

57
00:02:15,867 --> 00:02:17,600
And she needs someone with her.

58
00:02:17,733 --> 00:02:18,600
That's what Dad's thinking.

59
00:02:18,733 --> 00:02:20,300
She might try something again.

60
00:02:21,967 --> 00:02:23,400
Sorry, okay?

61
00:02:23,533 --> 00:02:24,767
Maybe it sounds harsh...

62
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:28,867
but Dad should just let Hazel

63
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:30,600
do whatever she wants.

64
00:02:31,667 --> 00:02:34,233
He has no responsibility
toward her anymore.

65
00:02:34,367 --> 00:02:38,100
Andrea, they're not even
annulled yet.

66
00:02:38,233 --> 00:02:40,033
Whatever we do,
they're still married.

67
00:02:42,133 --> 00:02:43,433
And Jessica is gone.

68
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:47,700
Dad doesn't want
another tragedy.

69
00:02:49,300 --> 00:02:50,333
What if...

70
00:02:51,500 --> 00:02:53,900
What if Dad left because of me?

71
00:02:55,700 --> 00:02:57,133
Because he's angry at me?

72
00:02:57,267 --> 00:02:58,433
No, no, no, Coleen.

73
00:02:58,767 --> 00:03:01,000
That's not
what it means, Coleen.

74
00:03:01,133 --> 00:03:03,433
And why would Dad be mad at you?

75
00:03:04,833 --> 00:03:08,900
Maybe he believed Hazel
that I really pushed Jessica.

76
00:03:09,033 --> 00:03:10,300
Dear, no.

77
00:03:11,767 --> 00:03:13,400
Dad trusts you.

78
00:03:14,467 --> 00:03:16,467
What if he only said that?

79
00:03:17,733 --> 00:03:19,433
What if he can't
accept me anymore

80
00:03:19,567 --> 00:03:23,333
because he thinks
I killed Jessica?

81
00:03:39,167 --> 00:03:40,367
Good morning!

82
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:44,967
I'm here now, Hazel.

83
00:03:46,067 --> 00:03:47,300
I kept my end of the deal.

84
00:03:48,967 --> 00:03:50,800
When will Timo withdraw
his statement?

85
00:03:51,667 --> 00:03:52,667
Come on, Manuel.

86
00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:54,633
Relax!

87
00:03:54,767 --> 00:03:56,333
Why are you in such a hurry?

88
00:03:56,667 --> 00:03:58,100
Patience is a virtue.

89
00:03:58,233 --> 00:03:59,633
- Come on.
- Hazel, when?

90
00:03:59,767 --> 00:04:00,733
Tell me when.

91
00:04:01,733 --> 00:04:03,333
It's still early.

92
00:04:03,467 --> 00:04:04,667
Don't worry.

93
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:07,000
I won't break my promise.

94
00:04:07,133 --> 00:04:08,800
But for now, eat first, okay?

95
00:04:08,933 --> 00:04:10,400
Come on, breakfast is good.

96
00:04:10,533 --> 00:04:11,800
- Come on.
- I'm not hungry.

97
00:04:12,567 --> 00:04:13,800
Huh?

98
00:04:15,433 --> 00:04:16,433
Manuel!

99
00:04:16,567 --> 00:04:18,700
You need to eat
before you take your medicine.

100
00:04:24,267 --> 00:04:25,500
Patience.

101
00:04:25,633 --> 00:04:27,733
Patience, Hazel.

102
00:04:29,567 --> 00:04:30,933
Relax, don't take it to heart.

103
00:04:32,867 --> 00:04:34,267
His heart
will soften eventually.

104
00:04:35,333 --> 00:04:37,233
What matters is I have you back.

105
00:04:38,633 --> 00:04:42,233
I don't care if Felma keeps
saying she is the one you love.

106
00:04:42,367 --> 00:04:43,867
Because Manuel is with me now.

107
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:53,200
You already talked
to Diana, right?

108
00:04:53,333 --> 00:04:54,967
About withdrawing
your statement?

109
00:04:55,967 --> 00:04:56,967
Yes, Ma'am.

110
00:04:58,367 --> 00:05:01,100
But, Ma'am, I'm scared.

111
00:05:01,633 --> 00:05:04,033
I already lied,
and now I'll take it back?

112
00:05:04,967 --> 00:05:06,633
Isn't that perjury?

113
00:05:06,767 --> 00:05:08,200
My case will get worse.

114
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:09,833
Just say...

115
00:05:10,967 --> 00:05:13,100
you were looking
or someone to blame.

116
00:05:13,233 --> 00:05:21,633
Because you thought it might
lessen your sentence.

117
00:05:21,767 --> 00:05:24,100
Why? You don't want to?

118
00:05:26,867 --> 00:05:27,700
Timo...

119
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:30,633
I didn't want to do this.

120
00:05:31,733 --> 00:05:33,267
Don't push me.

121
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:36,867
Do you know I can make
your life here miserable?

122
00:05:38,333 --> 00:05:39,967
I even mentioned that to Diana.

123
00:05:41,500 --> 00:05:42,567
I know, Ma'am.

124
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:46,300
That's why she was forced
to convince me, right?

125
00:05:48,233 --> 00:05:49,300
There you go.

126
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:53,167
Then withdraw your statement.

127
00:05:54,900 --> 00:05:59,367
Because it's not
just your life I can ruin...

128
00:05:59,500 --> 00:06:04,833
or make miserable,
but also your child's.

129
00:06:04,967 --> 00:06:07,467
Your children's and your wife's.

130
00:06:10,700 --> 00:06:12,500
I'm a dangerous enemy, Timo.

131
00:06:14,233 --> 00:06:17,067
So if you don't want
trouble for your family,

132
00:06:18,300 --> 00:06:20,233
just do what I want.

133
00:06:21,733 --> 00:06:24,367
Oh, by the way,
I have good news.

134
00:06:24,500 --> 00:06:26,967
I arranged for your wife
to give birth

135
00:06:27,100 --> 00:06:29,233
at Southcrest Premier Hospital.

136
00:06:29,367 --> 00:06:31,067
Oh, see? Fancy.

137
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:32,967
She won't have to suffer.

138
00:06:40,067 --> 00:06:42,267
What? Manual went back to...

139
00:06:44,133 --> 00:06:45,100
Hazel?!

140
00:06:47,467 --> 00:06:49,233
- Oh no!
- Oh, Auntie.

141
00:06:49,667 --> 00:06:50,600
Auntie, what are you doing?

142
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:52,433
You're calling Mom?

143
00:06:52,567 --> 00:06:53,500
Yes.

144
00:06:53,633 --> 00:06:54,700
Don't.

145
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,067
Don't call her.

146
00:06:57,733 --> 00:06:59,267
She won't answer anyway.

147
00:07:01,833 --> 00:07:03,467
She won't even talk to us.

148
00:07:06,533 --> 00:07:07,767
How's your mom?

149
00:07:10,433 --> 00:07:12,333
She's locked herself
in her room.

150
00:07:14,900 --> 00:07:16,233
She won't come out.

151
00:07:18,167 --> 00:07:19,533
We just let her be.

152
00:07:21,700 --> 00:07:22,767
Poor thing.

153
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:24,433
Here we go again.

154
00:07:24,567 --> 00:07:26,167
Your mom's suffering again.

155
00:07:27,433 --> 00:07:28,467
Ah! Hazel.

156
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:30,700
Hazel is the reason
for all this.

157
00:07:30,833 --> 00:07:32,100
That wretched little pest!

158
00:07:32,233 --> 00:07:33,700
Oh my! Andeng, come here!

159
00:07:33,833 --> 00:07:35,200
Come with me,
I'm going after her!

160
00:07:35,333 --> 00:07:36,567
Auntie, what for?

161
00:07:37,667 --> 00:07:39,133
Dad has already made
his decision.

162
00:07:39,767 --> 00:07:41,700
What can we do?

163
00:07:44,967 --> 00:07:45,933
What is this?

164
00:07:46,067 --> 00:07:47,133
I don't get it.

165
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:48,400
I don't understand Manuel.

166
00:07:48,533 --> 00:07:51,100
What was he thinking? Huh?

167
00:07:51,233 --> 00:07:53,267
Your dad is really
getting on my nerves!

168
00:07:54,900 --> 00:07:57,567
But wait...

169
00:07:57,700 --> 00:07:59,500
<i>What are you
and Hazel doing here?</i>

170
00:07:59,633 --> 00:08:03,200
<i>How did you know Manuel
and Felma were here, huh?</i>

171
00:08:03,333 --> 00:08:06,000
<i>- Yes, how?!
- Because of you!</i>

172
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:08,533
Because of what, Auntie?

173
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:12,067
Andrea.

174
00:08:13,500 --> 00:08:14,867
Is what Jeffrey said true?

175
00:08:15,967 --> 00:08:18,200
Manuel went back to Hazel again?

176
00:08:19,967 --> 00:08:21,400
He left you all again?

177
00:08:23,967 --> 00:08:25,233
Noah, excuse me.

178
00:08:27,633 --> 00:08:28,800
Hello, Abel?

179
00:08:28,933 --> 00:08:30,667
Come to FMP.

180
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:32,167
Right now!

181
00:08:39,633 --> 00:08:42,033
Why would Manuel do this now?

182
00:08:42,167 --> 00:08:44,100
When your whole family is
already going through something?

183
00:08:44,833 --> 00:08:45,833
Dear, how's Coleen?

184
00:08:45,967 --> 00:08:47,167
Well...

185
00:08:48,133 --> 00:08:49,200
She's not okay.

186
00:08:50,733 --> 00:08:53,300
She thinks Dad believes Hazel.

187
00:08:54,767 --> 00:08:56,500
That she really pushed Jessica.

188
00:08:57,767 --> 00:08:59,167
What about Felma?

189
00:08:59,300 --> 00:09:00,700
How's your mom?

190
00:09:00,833 --> 00:09:04,033
It feels like we're back
to the old days, Uncle.

191
00:09:05,267 --> 00:09:07,300
The first time Dad left us.

192
00:09:08,467 --> 00:09:11,133
We can't talk
to Mom properly again.

193
00:09:13,667 --> 00:09:15,967
We're struggling again.

194
00:09:31,733 --> 00:09:34,967
So... it's a done deal
with Timo?

195
00:09:35,100 --> 00:09:36,800
He'll recant his statement?

196
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:39,067
Yes.

197
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:40,400
He should, right?

198
00:09:40,533 --> 00:09:42,600
I'm helping his wife
and kids, after all.

199
00:09:44,967 --> 00:09:46,833
Helping or paying them?

200
00:09:48,467 --> 00:09:51,233
Well, what's the difference?

201
00:09:52,767 --> 00:09:56,067
When people are desperate,
they come with a price.

202
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:57,400
Anyone can be bought.

203
00:09:58,200 --> 00:09:59,767
No matter how decent they are.

204
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,300
So you cornered Timo?

205
00:10:02,433 --> 00:10:03,467
Threatened him?

206
00:10:04,367 --> 00:10:06,767
Oh, pretty much.

207
00:10:06,900 --> 00:10:09,267
And look, he cooperated.

208
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:11,533
Because if he didn't,
if he fought back,

209
00:10:11,667 --> 00:10:13,933
I'd be forced to use violence.

210
00:10:14,067 --> 00:10:15,000
And that would be sad.

211
00:10:15,133 --> 00:10:16,967
His family
would get dragged into it.

212
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:18,500
Hazel...

213
00:10:18,633 --> 00:10:21,900
- What?
- Violence brings no good.

214
00:10:22,033 --> 00:10:23,967
Haven't you learned?

215
00:10:24,100 --> 00:10:27,033
Huh? You saw
what happened to you.

216
00:10:27,167 --> 00:10:29,867
Because of the violence
you caused,

217
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:32,367
you lost your child.

218
00:10:32,500 --> 00:10:34,033
Oh, please.

219
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:35,833
You think I want to do all this?

220
00:10:36,900 --> 00:10:38,400
But what choice do I have?

221
00:10:38,533 --> 00:10:40,833
I'm forced to fight,
to be violent,

222
00:10:40,967 --> 00:10:43,033
because of the villains
in my life.

223
00:10:43,167 --> 00:10:45,433
Especially Felma,
she stole Manuel from me.

224
00:10:47,367 --> 00:10:50,100
Oh, stop giving me that look.

225
00:10:50,233 --> 00:10:51,433
That's how it is, Alice.

226
00:10:51,567 --> 00:10:53,633
You do everything
for the person you love.

227
00:10:53,767 --> 00:10:55,233
That's how it should be.

228
00:10:55,367 --> 00:10:56,933
Even if you hurt people?

229
00:10:57,067 --> 00:10:59,300
That's not love,
that's obsession.

230
00:11:00,333 --> 00:11:01,333
Call it whatever you want.

231
00:11:01,467 --> 00:11:03,867
What matters is that
I got my husband back.

232
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,933
But you used your own child.

233
00:11:06,067 --> 00:11:07,367
My god, Hazel.

234
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:10,000
It's like Jessica's death
means nothing to you.

235
00:11:11,967 --> 00:11:13,067
That's not true.

236
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:14,300
Isn't it?

237
00:11:14,433 --> 00:11:17,567
Because, from what I see,
everything you do

238
00:11:17,700 --> 00:11:21,833
has nothing to do
with justice for Jessica.

239
00:11:21,967 --> 00:11:25,367
It's just all about you
taking Manuel back!

240
00:11:38,267 --> 00:11:40,567
Your friend!

241
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:42,833
What? I'm already calling him!

242
00:11:43,900 --> 00:11:46,533
Bro, what happened?

243
00:11:46,667 --> 00:11:48,433
Why are you with Hazel again?

244
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:50,267
Did she force you?

245
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:51,833
<i>Do you want us
to go rescue you again?</i>

246
00:11:51,967 --> 00:11:53,467
No, bro, It's true.

247
00:11:53,600 --> 00:11:54,867
It was really my decision.

248
00:11:55,300 --> 00:11:58,100
<i>So what now? Your decision
to hurt your fam...</i>

249
00:11:59,300 --> 00:12:00,467
Your own family again?

250
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:01,833
Darling...

251
00:12:01,967 --> 00:12:03,433
<i>can you not interrupt
for a second?</i>

252
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:05,667
<i> What is it, Manuel?</i>

253
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:06,867
Huh?

254
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:08,433
Tell me the truth

255
00:12:08,567 --> 00:12:11,067
because I'm so confused
right now.

256
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:13,833
I want an explanation,
and it better

257
00:12:13,967 --> 00:12:16,300
be a good one!

258
00:12:16,467 --> 00:12:18,467
Hey! I've heard that in a movie.

259
00:12:18,600 --> 00:12:19,767
You just translated it into
Tagalog.

260
00:12:20,333 --> 00:12:21,933
<i> Can you go over there first?</i>

261
00:12:22,067 --> 00:12:24,500
<i>I want to hear
my friend's explanation.</i>

262
00:12:25,533 --> 00:12:26,733
No, bro.

263
00:12:26,867 --> 00:12:29,500
I'm married to Hazel, right?

264
00:12:29,633 --> 00:12:32,067
So, of course,
I have obligations to her.

265
00:12:32,500 --> 00:12:34,667
Especially now that
our child has died.

266
00:12:34,800 --> 00:12:36,767
Of course, she needs me.

267
00:12:36,900 --> 00:12:38,967
<i> Tell me the truth, Manuel.</i>

268
00:12:39,100 --> 00:12:40,833
Did Hazel threaten you?

269
00:12:40,967 --> 00:12:41,800
What did she say?

270
00:12:41,933 --> 00:12:44,867
She'd massacre Felma
and your kids? Huh?

271
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:46,367
<i> Where's that little demon?</i>

272
00:12:46,500 --> 00:12:48,267
<i> Let us talk to her!</i>

273
00:12:48,433 --> 00:12:50,500
I heard you.

274
00:12:51,867 --> 00:12:53,067
I'm here.

275
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:57,700
<i>Paz, Abel, please
don't be angry at Manuel.</i>

276
00:12:57,833 --> 00:13:00,800
Can we just respect
his decision?

277
00:13:00,933 --> 00:13:03,700
And maybe give us a chance

278
00:13:03,833 --> 00:13:06,600
to fix our relationship.

279
00:13:06,733 --> 00:13:08,933
We got back together
because of Jessica.

280
00:13:09,067 --> 00:13:10,367
This is for our daughter.

281
00:13:11,033 --> 00:13:13,133
"For our daughter"?

282
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:15,467
Hazel, don't you dare
use my godchild.

283
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:17,100
Jessica is dead.

284
00:13:17,633 --> 00:13:19,800
We dreamed of her.

285
00:13:20,033 --> 00:13:22,033
She told Manuel
to take care of me.

286
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:24,667
Really?
Stop it, Hazel.

287
00:13:24,800 --> 00:13:27,400
With all the lies you've fed us,

288
00:13:27,533 --> 00:13:29,967
you think we'll believe you now?

289
00:13:30,100 --> 00:13:32,733
<i> Tell me the truth, you witch!</i>

290
00:13:32,867 --> 00:13:35,633
Tell us, Hazel!
What did you do to Manuel?

291
00:13:35,767 --> 00:13:38,200
Did you curse him?
Hex him? Bewitch him?

292
00:13:38,333 --> 00:13:40,667
<i> Paz, Paz, enough.</i>

293
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:43,967
Hazel had nothing to do
with my decision.

294
00:13:45,033 --> 00:13:46,833
I came back to her on my own.

295
00:13:47,567 --> 00:13:50,267
Oh, really? That's your final
answer, Manuel?

296
00:13:50,400 --> 00:13:52,400
That you went back
to that evil woman?

297
00:13:52,533 --> 00:13:54,067
Fine! Then here's
what I'll say to you

298
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:56,600
You're an animal!
A soulless,

299
00:13:56,767 --> 00:13:58,967
<i> heartless, useless animal!</i>

300
00:13:59,100 --> 00:14:01,700
So that's why Hazel
was at the resort,

301
00:14:01,833 --> 00:14:03,833
<i> because you had an agreement!</i>

302
00:14:08,800 --> 00:14:10,567
You went to the resort?

303
00:14:18,333 --> 00:14:20,133
Promise me this, darling.

304
00:14:20,267 --> 00:14:23,767
Starting today, you will never
talk to Manuel again.

305
00:14:23,900 --> 00:14:26,733
And if he calls,
you won't answer.

306
00:14:26,867 --> 00:14:28,633
End it! Cut all ties with him.

307
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:30,067
Friendship over.

308
00:14:32,367 --> 00:14:33,433
Unbelievable.

309
00:14:33,567 --> 00:14:35,067
Manuel is such a traitor.

310
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:38,833
He came home to the Philippines
just to fool

311
00:14:38,967 --> 00:14:40,900
his family, to hurt them again!

312
00:14:41,967 --> 00:14:46,800
He said he'd get his marriage
to Hazel annulled

313
00:14:46,933 --> 00:14:48,233
so he could go back to Felma!

314
00:14:48,367 --> 00:14:50,233
But what did he do?

315
00:14:50,367 --> 00:14:52,567
Traitor! Full of false hopes!

316
00:14:53,967 --> 00:14:56,200
I'm so angry at Manuel!

317
00:14:56,333 --> 00:14:58,633
I'm furious!

318
00:14:58,767 --> 00:15:02,167
Darling, you're too affected.

319
00:15:02,333 --> 00:15:04,133
You're acting like someone died.

320
00:15:04,267 --> 00:15:05,467
Were you the one
who got left behind?

321
00:15:05,967 --> 00:15:07,433
No.

322
00:15:07,567 --> 00:15:09,233
Then there you go.

323
00:15:09,367 --> 00:15:10,733
Don't be so dramatic.

324
00:15:10,867 --> 00:15:15,533
I'm just hurting for my friend.

325
00:15:15,667 --> 00:15:17,933
Because your friend hurt her!

326
00:15:18,067 --> 00:15:21,200
Darling, enough.

327
00:15:21,333 --> 00:15:24,300
I understand how you feel.

328
00:15:24,433 --> 00:15:26,267
But Darling, honestly,

329
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:29,367
your acting is Oscar-worthy.

330
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:30,667
Trying to be the star.

331
00:15:30,800 --> 00:15:32,133
Tone it down.

332
00:15:32,267 --> 00:15:34,633
Go for Best Supporting
Actress instead.

333
00:15:36,367 --> 00:15:37,567
Am I being dramatic, darling?

334
00:15:38,933 --> 00:15:40,067
Let's ask them.

335
00:15:48,267 --> 00:15:49,633
Hazel, I'm asking you.

336
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:52,867
Did you go to my family outing?

337
00:15:53,500 --> 00:15:55,100
What were you doing there?

338
00:15:56,433 --> 00:15:58,267
Sorry.

339
00:15:58,400 --> 00:16:00,033
I was just scared...

340
00:16:00,467 --> 00:16:02,933
Scared that Felma
might take you away.

341
00:16:04,333 --> 00:16:05,633
At the resort?

342
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:08,567
I'm sorry.

343
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:11,733
I wasn't thinking straight.

344
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:15,100
But I didn't
cause trouble, right?

345
00:16:15,867 --> 00:16:17,467
Felma and I only talked.

346
00:16:18,467 --> 00:16:21,167
Yes, Manuel, she explained

347
00:16:21,300 --> 00:16:24,867
that they just wanted to spend
one last day with you.

348
00:16:25,367 --> 00:16:27,933
And after that, the next day,

349
00:16:28,067 --> 00:16:29,467
she said she'd return you to me.

350
00:16:30,367 --> 00:16:32,367
She returned you willingly.

351
00:16:33,867 --> 00:16:35,067
Felma did that?

352
00:16:36,300 --> 00:16:37,767
Yes.

353
00:16:37,900 --> 00:16:39,000
Didn't she tell you?

354
00:16:40,200 --> 00:16:44,233
She even said,
"Manuel is all yours now."

355
00:16:55,067 --> 00:16:57,100
You're a liar, Dad.

356
00:17:00,033 --> 00:17:02,767
You said you believed me.

357
00:17:02,900 --> 00:17:05,000
<i> Is it true you pushed Jessica?</i>

358
00:17:05,133 --> 00:17:06,800
<i> Dad, I didn't.</i>

359
00:17:06,933 --> 00:17:10,167
<i> Then why are you surrendering?</i>

360
00:17:10,467 --> 00:17:12,600
<i>I'm sorry that
I couldn't save you.</i>

361
00:17:12,733 --> 00:17:15,533
<i> Coleen, I know your sister.</i>

362
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:18,333
<i>And in my heart, I know
she doesn't blame you.</i>

363
00:17:18,467 --> 00:17:20,700
<i>There's a subpoena already,
you're not alone.</i>

364
00:17:20,833 --> 00:17:21,967
<i> We're all fighting with you.</i>

365
00:17:22,100 --> 00:17:24,367
<i>We'll do everything
to defend you.</i>

366
00:17:24,500 --> 00:17:27,600
<i>She had no reason
to do anything bad</i>

367
00:17:27,733 --> 00:17:30,000
<i> or hurt Jessica, none.</i>

368
00:17:31,133 --> 00:17:33,233
But now, I guess
that wasn't true.

369
00:17:59,133 --> 00:18:00,000
Sir Noah, please come in.

370
00:18:00,133 --> 00:18:01,000
Hi, Didang.

371
00:18:01,133 --> 00:18:03,733
How are things here?

372
00:18:04,933 --> 00:18:05,967
How's Coleen?

373
00:18:06,333 --> 00:18:09,700
Sir, she hasn't been
leaving her room.

374
00:18:11,833 --> 00:18:13,467
What about Felma?

375
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:18,133
Well, Sir, it's bad news,
good news, then bad news again.

376
00:18:19,633 --> 00:18:23,900
Bad news, good news,
then bad news again?

377
00:18:24,067 --> 00:18:25,533
Here's the thing, Sir.

378
00:18:25,667 --> 00:18:29,500
Ma'am Felma hasn't been
coming out of her room,

379
00:18:29,633 --> 00:18:30,733
just like Coleen.

380
00:18:30,867 --> 00:18:32,700
It's been days.

381
00:18:32,833 --> 00:18:34,600
And she won't eat.

382
00:18:34,733 --> 00:18:37,333
She doesn't talk to anyone.

383
00:18:37,467 --> 00:18:39,767
We're all really worried.

384
00:18:41,133 --> 00:18:42,700
Andrea said the same thing.

385
00:18:42,833 --> 00:18:46,700
Then... what's the good news?

386
00:18:46,833 --> 00:18:49,933
Well... she came out earlier.

387
00:18:50,067 --> 00:18:53,167
And the other bad news?

388
00:18:53,433 --> 00:18:54,600
That's the thing, Sir.

389
00:18:54,733 --> 00:18:58,433
She came out, but food wasn't
the first thing she looked for.

390
00:18:58,600 --> 00:19:00,133
It was alcohol, Sir Noah.

391
00:19:11,500 --> 00:19:13,500
<i>She returned
you to me willingly.</i>

392
00:19:14,767 --> 00:19:18,200
<i>She even said,
"Manuel is all yours now."</i>

393
00:19:25,933 --> 00:19:27,133
Manuel?

394
00:19:28,933 --> 00:19:30,367
I prepared your food.

395
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:31,967
Come on, eat now.

396
00:19:33,667 --> 00:19:34,767
Don't treat me like a baby.

397
00:19:35,800 --> 00:19:37,133
I can feed myself.

398
00:19:38,333 --> 00:19:40,200
I just want to take care of you.

399
00:19:41,367 --> 00:19:46,667
Are you thinking
about Abel and Paz's call?

400
00:19:47,633 --> 00:19:51,700
Maybe next time,

401
00:19:51,833 --> 00:19:53,433
don't talk to them.

402
00:19:56,367 --> 00:19:58,167
Are you forbidding me, Hazel?

403
00:19:58,300 --> 00:20:03,867
If all they'll do is stress
you out, then why answer?

404
00:20:04,500 --> 00:20:06,633
I'm just protecting you, Manuel.

405
00:20:06,767 --> 00:20:09,833
And besides, let's focus

406
00:20:09,967 --> 00:20:12,633
on starting our new life.

407
00:20:12,767 --> 00:20:14,033
We owe it to our daughter.

408
00:20:15,033 --> 00:20:16,533
Let's not think
of anyone else for now.

409
00:20:17,933 --> 00:20:19,033
And what?

410
00:20:19,500 --> 00:20:21,967
So now I can't talk
to my family? My kids?

411
00:20:23,133 --> 00:20:25,933
Hold on, Hazel,
That wasn't part of the deal.

412
00:20:26,067 --> 00:20:27,533
What deal?

413
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:30,467
Didn't you say you didn't want
them to know

414
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:34,133
you're sacrificing yourself
to clear Coleen?

415
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:36,133
Because she might feel guilty?

416
00:20:37,300 --> 00:20:40,567
Manuel, your kids are angry
at you anyway.

417
00:20:40,700 --> 00:20:42,333
What else is there
to talk about?

418
00:20:44,733 --> 00:20:48,400
Better to let things
cool down first.

419
00:20:49,900 --> 00:20:55,800
Let them accept that you
and I are meant to be.

420
00:20:57,233 --> 00:20:59,300
And eventually, you know,

421
00:20:59,433 --> 00:21:02,700
a day will come,
we'll all get along.

422
00:21:03,733 --> 00:21:05,433
Even me and Felma.

423
00:21:05,567 --> 00:21:08,600
There are wives and mistresses

424
00:21:08,767 --> 00:21:10,467
who end up getting along, right?

425
00:21:10,600 --> 00:21:12,667
I told you not to call
Felma a mistress!

426
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:18,433
Yes, Hazel, you're my wife.

427
00:21:19,333 --> 00:21:20,200
On paper.

428
00:21:20,333 --> 00:21:22,167
It's Felma...
Felma is the one I love.

429
00:21:28,400 --> 00:21:30,233
Hazel, let me be clear.

430
00:21:31,767 --> 00:21:34,233
I came back because
you said you'd help me

431
00:21:34,367 --> 00:21:36,000
clear Coleen's name.

432
00:21:37,200 --> 00:21:39,167
That doesn't mean I love you.

433
00:21:42,133 --> 00:21:43,500
I know.

434
00:21:46,667 --> 00:21:47,867
I know that, Manuel.

435
00:21:49,600 --> 00:21:51,467
But don't rub it in.

436
00:21:53,200 --> 00:21:56,767
It still hurts.

437
00:22:00,033 --> 00:22:01,400
I just hope, Manuel...

438
00:22:03,967 --> 00:22:05,567
you don't close
your heart completely.

439
00:22:08,833 --> 00:22:10,167
I'll prove to you

440
00:22:11,867 --> 00:22:13,633
that I'm still worthy
of your love.

441
00:22:15,400 --> 00:22:19,600
I can even turn my back
on justice for our daughter...

442
00:22:21,533 --> 00:22:23,367
just to save
your child with Felma.

443
00:22:25,500 --> 00:22:28,100
So, please.

444
00:22:29,100 --> 00:22:30,567
I'm only asking
one simple thing.

445
00:22:31,833 --> 00:22:33,467
Don't talk to them for now.

446
00:22:34,300 --> 00:22:35,267
That's all.

447
00:22:36,733 --> 00:22:39,100
I hope you grant me that,
because if you don't...

448
00:22:40,867 --> 00:22:42,300
I'm sorry, but...

449
00:22:45,167 --> 00:22:47,633
I might stop convincing Timo

450
00:22:49,067 --> 00:22:51,533
to withdraw his statement
against Coleen.

451
00:22:52,567 --> 00:22:54,500
He's already having second
thoughts anyway.

452
00:22:56,833 --> 00:22:58,300
Are you threatening me, Hazel?

453
00:22:58,967 --> 00:23:00,533
No, Manuel.

454
00:23:02,567 --> 00:23:03,833
But it's unfair.

455
00:23:06,233 --> 00:23:07,800
I'm doing everything, right?

456
00:23:08,967 --> 00:23:10,233
For you.

457
00:23:10,367 --> 00:23:11,567
For your child.

458
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:16,433
And you can't even grant me
this one simple request.

459
00:23:17,600 --> 00:23:19,167
Be fair to me.

460
00:23:20,433 --> 00:23:21,533
Because if not...

461
00:23:22,600 --> 00:23:23,867
maybe you should...

462
00:23:25,867 --> 00:23:27,200
just go back to them.

463
00:23:29,433 --> 00:23:31,733
Maybe we should just end
our agreement.

464
00:23:37,567 --> 00:23:38,433
Why the long face?

465
00:23:38,567 --> 00:23:39,767
Dad isn't answering.

466
00:23:39,900 --> 00:23:42,133
Maybe his phone was confiscated.

467
00:23:42,267 --> 00:23:43,233
I expected that.

468
00:23:43,367 --> 00:23:44,833
That's why I gave Dad
an extra phone.

469
00:23:49,867 --> 00:23:52,533
This is fun!
There are so many of us!

470
00:23:52,667 --> 00:23:53,567
You're so hyper.

471
00:23:53,700 --> 00:23:55,433
Didang! What is that?

472
00:23:55,600 --> 00:23:57,400
Ma'am, that's the dish
you asked me to cook.

473
00:23:57,533 --> 00:23:58,433
No!

474
00:23:58,567 --> 00:24:00,267
What are you trying to imply?

475
00:24:00,400 --> 00:24:01,767
That I'm lying?
